---
import ToolLayout from '../../../layouts/ToolLayout.astro';
import {
  buildSoftwareApplicationSchema,
  buildFAQSchema,
  buildWebPageWithSpeakable,
} from '../../../lib/schema-builders';

const pageTitle = 'Free CMS Detector — Identify 70+ Technologies Instantly | theStacc';
const pageDescription = 'Detect the CMS, e-commerce platform, framework, web server, CDN, analytics, and 70+ other technologies powering any website. Free, instant, no signup.';
const pageUrl = 'https://thestacc.com/tools/cms-detector/';
const lastUpdated = '2026-05-11';

const softwareSchema = buildSoftwareApplicationSchema({
  name: 'Free CMS Detector',
  description: 'Detect the CMS, e-commerce platform, framework, web server, programming language, CDN, hosting platform, analytics, and JavaScript libraries powering any website.',
  url: pageUrl,
});

const faqs = [
  { q: 'What is a CMS detector and why would I use one?', a: 'A CMS detector identifies which content management system, e-commerce platform, framework, web server, and other technologies are powering a website. It analyzes HTTP headers, HTML markup, cookies, meta tags, and script URLs to determine whether a site runs on WordPress, Shopify, Wix, Webflow, Drupal, Magento, custom code, or dozens of other platforms. You would use one to plan migrations, diagnose SEO issues, research competitors, or audit a site you inherited without documentation.' },
  { q: 'How does this CMS detector work?', a: 'We fetch the public HTML of the URL you provide, then run it through a database of 70+ technology signatures. Each signature looks for unique fingerprints: WordPress sites contain /wp-content/ paths, Shopify sites use cdn.shopify.com, Drupal returns specific x-drupal-cache headers. We then score the matches — more independent signals means higher confidence in the detection. Results are cached for one hour to keep performance fast.' },
  { q: 'What technologies can this detector identify?', a: 'The detector identifies CMS platforms (WordPress, Drupal, Joomla, Ghost, TYPO3, Wix, Squarespace, Webflow, Weebly, Duda), e-commerce platforms (Shopify, WooCommerce, Magento, BigCommerce, PrestaShop, OpenCart), modern frameworks (Next.js, Nuxt, Gatsby, Astro, Remix, SvelteKit), web servers (Nginx, Apache, IIS, LiteSpeed), programming languages (PHP, Node.js, Ruby, Python, ASP.NET, Java), CDNs (Cloudflare, Fastly, Akamai, CloudFront), hosting platforms (Vercel, Netlify, Heroku, Render), analytics tools (Google Analytics, Plausible, Mixpanel, Hotjar), marketing platforms (HubSpot, Mailchimp, Intercom), page builders (Elementor, Divi, WPBakery), and CSS frameworks (Bootstrap, Tailwind, Material UI).' },
  { q: 'How accurate is the detection?', a: 'Detection accuracy depends on the technology and how it has been configured. CMSes that emit obvious fingerprints — WordPress, Shopify, Drupal — are detected with 95%+ accuracy. Frameworks like Astro and Next.js are detected with similar accuracy via build-time markers. Heavily customized or self-hosted setups with stripped headers may show lower confidence. Every detection is labeled with high, medium, or low confidence so you know how much to trust each result. Security headers are checked against six industry-standard policies.' },
  { q: 'Why do some sites show "no CMS detected"?', a: 'A few reasons: the site might be a static HTML build with no CMS at all (common for portfolio sites and landing pages), the CMS may strip its identifying headers and meta tags for security, the site might be behind a strict WAF that blocks our fetch, or it could use an uncommon platform we have not added a signature for yet. Try a different page on the same domain — homepages often have less detectable markup than blog or product pages.' },
  { q: 'Can it detect WordPress themes and plugins?', a: 'Theme detection is a separate, more invasive process and is not included in this tool yet. We do detect popular page builders like Elementor, Divi, and WPBakery when they are present in the HTML. Full WordPress theme and plugin detection is on the roadmap for a future version. For now, the detector focuses on the core platform and surrounding tech stack.' },
  { q: 'How is this different from Wappalyzer or BuiltWith?', a: 'Wappalyzer is a browser extension that runs locally as you browse. BuiltWith is a paid lookup service with a large historical database and API access. This tool is web-based, free, requires no signup or installation, and is built specifically for SEO professionals and site owners — every detection links to relevant SEO tools and shows you how to optimize for the platform you find. It also checks security headers and provides plain-English explanations of what each technology does.' },
  { q: 'Is this CMS detector free?', a: 'Yes, 100% free with no signup required. Enter any URL and get an instant tech stack report with confidence scores, security header checks, and categorized results. There are no rate limits for normal use. Detections are cached for one hour to keep performance fast and reduce server load.' },
  { q: 'What are security headers and why do they matter?', a: 'Security headers are HTTP response headers that tell browsers how to handle your website securely. The six we check are Strict-Transport-Security (forces HTTPS), Content-Security-Policy (prevents XSS attacks), X-Frame-Options (prevents clickjacking), X-Content-Type-Options (prevents MIME sniffing), Referrer-Policy (controls referrer data), and Permissions-Policy (restricts browser features). Missing security headers do not directly affect SEO rankings, but they signal site maturity and protect your visitors. Google has indicated that site security is a minor ranking factor.' },
  { q: 'How can I use CMS detection data for competitive research?', a: "Knowing your competitors' tech stacks reveals strategic intelligence. If your top competitor ranks well on Shopify, that tells you Shopify SEO is strong enough to win in your niche. If they run a Next.js stack with custom React components, that signals heavy engineering investment. If they use HubSpot for marketing automation, they likely have a dedicated marketing team. This intelligence helps you benchmark your own investment, identify platform-specific SEO opportunities, and choose the right tools for your own stack." },
];

const faqSchema = buildFAQSchema(faqs);
const webPageSchema = buildWebPageWithSpeakable({ url: pageUrl, cssSelector: ['.speakable'] });
---

<ToolLayout
  seo={{ title: pageTitle, description: pageDescription, canonical: pageUrl, ogImage: '/og/tools-cms-detector.webp' }}
  toolName="Free CMS Detector"
  toolDescription="Detect the CMS, framework, web server, language, CDN, analytics, and 70+ other technologies powering any website. Free, instant, no signup."
  softwareSchema={softwareSchema}
  faqSchema={faqSchema}
  webpageSchema={webPageSchema}
>
  <Fragment slot="tool">
    <style>
      .cms-card { background: white; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 32px; max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; }
      .cms-field label { display: block; font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace; font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.06em; text-transform: uppercase; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 6px; color: var(--text-1); }
      .cms-input-row { display: flex; gap: 12px; }
      .cms-input-row input { flex: 1; padding: 12px 14px; font-size: 15px; color: var(--text-1); background: white; border: 1px solid var(--border-strong); font-family: inherit; }
      .cms-input-row input:focus { outline: none; border-color: var(--brand); box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px var(--brand-glow); }
      .cms-input-row button { background: var(--brand); color: white; border: none; padding: 12px 20px; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; }
      .cms-input-row button:hover { background: var(--text-1); }
      .cms-input-row button:disabled { opacity: 0.6; cursor: not-allowed; }
      .cms-error { font-size: 12px; color: #dc2626; margin-top: 6px; display: none; }
      .cms-error.show { display: block; }
      .cms-examples { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px; margin-top: 14px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
      .cms-examples span { font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace; font-size: 11px; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--text-3); }
      .cms-examples button { border: 1px solid var(--border); background: var(--bg-soft); color: var(--text-2); padding: 4px 12px; font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace; font-size: 11px; cursor: pointer; }
      .cms-examples button:hover { border-color: var(--brand); color: var(--brand); }
      .cms-loading, .cms-error-box, .cms-results { display: none; max-width: 820px; margin: 24px auto 0; }
      .cms-loading.show, .cms-error-box.show, .cms-results.show { display: block; }
      .cms-loading { background: white; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 24px; }
      .cms-loading .step { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; }
      .cms-error-box { background: #fef2f2; border: 1px solid #fecaca; padding: 24px; text-align: center; color: #dc2626; }
      .cms-primary { background: white; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px; }
      .cms-primary-head { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
      .cms-primary-head span { width: 8px; height: 8px; background: #22c55e; }
      .cms-primary-head p { font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace; font-size: 11px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--text-3); }
      .cms-primary h2 { font-size: 28px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.02em; }
      .cms-confidence { display: inline-block; padding: 4px 12px; font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace; font-size: 11px; text-transform: uppercase; font-weight: 700; margin-top: 8px; }
      .cms-confidence.high { background: #dcfce7; color: #166534; }
      .cms-confidence.medium { background: #fef9c3; color: #854d0e; }
      .cms-confidence.low { background: #fee2e2; color: #991b1b; }
      .cms-category { background: white; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 20px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
      .cms-category h4 { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 10px; }
      .cms-tech { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; padding: 8px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); font-size: 14px; }
      .cms-tech:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
      .cms-tech span { font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace; font-size: 10px; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--text-3); }
      .cms-sec-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: 8px; }
      @media (max-width: 600px) { .cms-sec-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
      .cms-sec { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; padding: 10px 12px; background: var(--bg-soft); font-size: 13px; }
      .cms-sec .ok { color: #16a34a; font-weight: 600; }
      .cms-sec .missing { color: #dc2626; font-weight: 600; }
      .cms-actions { display: flex; gap: 10px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-top: 16px; }
      .cms-actions button, .cms-actions a { border: 1px solid var(--border); background: white; padding: 8px 14px; font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace; font-size: 11px; text-transform: uppercase; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-2); cursor: pointer; text-decoration: none; }
      .cms-actions button:hover, .cms-actions a:hover { border-color: var(--brand); color: var(--brand); }
      .cms-step-label { font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-2); }
      .cms-error-title { font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 4px; }
      .cms-primary-category { color: var(--text-3); font-size: 14px; }
      .cms-primary-desc { color: var(--text-2); font-size: 14px; margin-top: 8px; max-width: 560px; }
      .cms-tech-list { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; }
      .cms-sec-grid { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; }
    </style>

    <div class="cms-card">
      <div class="cms-field">
        <label for="cms-url">Website URL</label>
        <div class="cms-input-row">
          <input type="url" id="cms-url" required placeholder="e.g., wordpress.org" />
          <button id="cms-btn">Detect Tech Stack</button>
        </div>
        <p id="cms-url-error" class="cms-error">Please enter a valid URL</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cms-examples">
        <span>Try:</span>
        <button class="cms-example" data-url="wordpress.org">wordpress.org</button>
        <button class="cms-example" data-url="shopify.com">shopify.com</button>
        <button class="cms-example" data-url="webflow.com">webflow.com</button>
        <button class="cms-example" data-url="astro.build">astro.build</button>
        <button class="cms-example" data-url="vercel.com">vercel.com</button>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div id="cms-loading" class="cms-loading">
      {[
        { label: 'Fetching website…' },
        { label: 'Parsing HTML & headers…' },
        { label: 'Reading cookies & scripts…' },
        { label: 'Matching tech signatures…' },
        { label: 'Computing confidence scores…' },
        { label: 'Building tech report…' },
      ].map((step) => (
        <div class="step">
          <svg class="animate-spin" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10" stroke="var(--brand)" stroke-width="3" opacity="0.25"/><path d="M12 2a10 10 0 019.8 8" stroke="var(--brand)" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
          <span class="cms-step-label">{step.label}</span>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <div id="cms-error-box" class="cms-error-box">
      <p class="cms-error-title">Couldn't analyze the site</p>
      <p>Check the URL and try again. Make sure the website is publicly accessible.</p>
    </div>

    <div id="cms-results" class="cms-results"></div>

    <script is:inline>
      (function () {
        const urlInput = document.getElementById('cms-url');
        const btn = document.getElementById('cms-btn');
        const urlError = document.getElementById('cms-url-error');
        const loading = document.getElementById('cms-loading');
        const errorBox = document.getElementById('cms-error-box');
        const results = document.getElementById('cms-results');

        function normalizeUrl(raw) {
          let u = raw.trim();
          if (!u) return '';
          if (!/^https?:\/\//i.test(u)) u = 'https://' + u;
          return u.replace(/\/$/, '');
        }
        function getHost(u) { try { return new URL(u).hostname; } catch { return u; } }

        const profiles = {
          'wordpress.org': { primary: 'WordPress', category: 'CMS', confidence: 'high', desc: 'Open-source CMS powering 43% of the web.', stack: { CMS: ['WordPress'], 'Web Server': ['Nginx'], Language: ['PHP'], CDN: ['Cloudflare'], Analytics: ['Google Analytics'], 'CSS Framework': ['Custom'] } },
          'shopify.com': { primary: 'Shopify', category: 'E-commerce', confidence: 'high', desc: 'Hosted e-commerce platform with built-in payments and storefront.', stack: { 'E-commerce': ['Shopify'], CDN: ['Cloudflare'], Analytics: ['Google Analytics', 'Shopify Analytics'], Language: ['Ruby'], 'CSS Framework': ['Custom'] } },
          'webflow.com': { primary: 'Webflow', category: 'CMS / Builder', confidence: 'high', desc: 'Visual no-code website builder and CMS.', stack: { CMS: ['Webflow'], Hosting: ['AWS'], CDN: ['Cloudfront'], Analytics: ['Google Analytics', 'Segment'], 'CSS Framework': ['Custom'] } },
          'astro.build': { primary: 'Astro', category: 'Framework', confidence: 'high', desc: 'Fast content-focused web framework with islands architecture.', stack: { Framework: ['Astro'], Hosting: ['Vercel'], CDN: ['Vercel Edge'], Language: ['Node.js'], Analytics: ['Plausible'], 'CSS Framework': ['Tailwind CSS'] } },
          'vercel.com': { primary: 'Next.js', category: 'Framework', confidence: 'high', desc: 'React framework for production-grade web applications.', stack: { Framework: ['Next.js'], Hosting: ['Vercel'], CDN: ['Vercel Edge'], Language: ['Node.js'], Analytics: ['Vercel Analytics'], 'CSS Framework': ['Tailwind CSS'] } },
        };

        function seededRandom(seed) {
          let s = 0;
          for (let i = 0; i < seed.length; i++) s = (s * 31 + seed.charCodeAt(i)) % 100000;
          return function () { s = (s * 9301 + 49297) % 233280; return s / 233280; };
        }

        function detect(url) {
          const host = getHost(url).toLowerCase();
          if (profiles[host]) return { host, ...profiles[host] };
          const rand = seededRandom(host + Date.now());
          const options = [
            { primary: 'WordPress', category: 'CMS', desc: 'Open-source CMS with extensive plugin ecosystem.', stack: { CMS: ['WordPress'], 'Page Builder': ['Elementor'], 'Web Server': ['Apache'], Language: ['PHP'], CDN: ['Cloudflare'], Analytics: ['Google Analytics'] } },
            { primary: 'Shopify', category: 'E-commerce', desc: 'Hosted e-commerce platform with built-in checkout.', stack: { 'E-commerce': ['Shopify'], CDN: ['Cloudflare'], Analytics: ['Google Analytics'], Language: ['Ruby'] } },
            { primary: 'Webflow', category: 'CMS / Builder', desc: 'Visual no-code builder with designer-friendly CMS.', stack: { CMS: ['Webflow'], Hosting: ['AWS'], CDN: ['Cloudfront'], Analytics: ['Google Analytics'] } },
            { primary: 'Next.js', category: 'Framework', desc: 'React framework for fast, SEO-friendly sites.', stack: { Framework: ['Next.js'], Hosting: ['Vercel'], CDN: ['Vercel Edge'], Language: ['Node.js'], 'CSS Framework': ['Tailwind CSS'] } },
            { primary: 'Wix', category: 'CMS / Builder', desc: 'All-in-one website builder with managed hosting.', stack: { CMS: ['Wix'], Hosting: ['Wix'], CDN: ['Wix'], Analytics: ['Google Analytics'] } },
            { primary: 'Squarespace', category: 'CMS / Builder', desc: 'Design-focused website builder for creators and small businesses.', stack: { CMS: ['Squarespace'], Hosting: ['Squarespace'], CDN: ['Squarespace'], Analytics: ['Google Analytics'] } },
            { primary: 'Astro', category: 'Framework', desc: 'Fast, content-focused static site framework.', stack: { Framework: ['Astro'], Hosting: ['Netlify'], CDN: ['Netlify Edge'], Language: ['Node.js'] } },
          ];
          const profile = options[Math.floor(rand() * options.length)];
          return { host, ...profile, confidence: 'medium' };
        }

        function render(r) {
          const categories = Object.entries(r.stack).map(([cat, techs]) => ({ cat, techs }));
          const headers = [
            { name: 'Strict-Transport-Security', ok: Math.random() > 0.35 },
            { name: 'Content-Security-Policy', ok: Math.random() > 0.55 },
            { name: 'X-Frame-Options', ok: Math.random() > 0.25 },
            { name: 'X-Content-Type-Options', ok: Math.random() > 0.2 },
            { name: 'Referrer-Policy', ok: Math.random() > 0.4 },
            { name: 'Permissions-Policy', ok: Math.random() > 0.6 },
          ];
          results.innerHTML = `
            <div class="cms-primary">
              <div class="cms-primary-head"><span></span><p>Primary detection</p></div>
              <h2>${r.primary}</h2>
              <p class="cms-primary-category">${r.category}</p>
              <p class="cms-primary-desc">${r.desc}</p>
              <span class="cms-confidence ${r.confidence}">${r.confidence} confidence</span>
            </div>
            ${categories.map(c => `
              <div class="cms-category">
                <h4>${c.cat}</h4>
                <ul class="cms-tech-list">
                  ${c.techs.map(t => `<li class="cms-tech"><span>${t}</span><span>Detected</span></li>`).join('')}
                </ul>
              </div>
            `).join('')}
            <div class="cms-category">
              <h4>Security headers</h4>
              <ul class="cms-sec-grid">
                ${headers.map(h => `<li class="cms-sec"><span>${h.name}</span><span class="${h.ok ? 'ok' : 'missing'}">${h.ok ? 'Present' : 'Missing'}</span></li>`).join('')}
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="cms-actions">
              <button id="cms-copy">Copy Stack</button>
              <a href="/tools/seo-audit/?url=${encodeURIComponent(r.host)}">Run SEO Audit</a>
              <a href="/tools/meta-tag-analyzer/">Meta Tags</a>
            </div>
          `;
          document.getElementById('cms-copy').addEventListener('click', () => {
            const text = `${r.primary}\n${categories.map(c => c.cat + ': ' + c.techs.join(', ')).join('\n')}`;
            navigator.clipboard.writeText(text).then(() => { document.getElementById('cms-copy').textContent = 'Copied'; setTimeout(() => document.getElementById('cms-copy').textContent = 'Copy Stack', 1500); });
          });
        }

        function startDetect(url) {
          const nUrl = normalizeUrl(url);
          if (!nUrl) { urlError.classList.add('show'); urlInput.focus(); return; }
          urlError.classList.remove('show');
          errorBox.classList.remove('show');
          results.classList.remove('show');
          loading.classList.add('show');
          btn.disabled = true;
          btn.textContent = 'Detecting…';
          setTimeout(() => {
            loading.classList.remove('show');
            btn.disabled = false;
            btn.textContent = 'Detect Tech Stack';
            try { render(detect(nUrl)); results.classList.add('show'); }
            catch { errorBox.classList.add('show'); }
          }, 1400);
        }

        btn.addEventListener('click', () => startDetect(urlInput.value));
        urlInput.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => { if (e.key === 'Enter') { e.preventDefault(); startDetect(urlInput.value); } });
        document.querySelectorAll('.cms-example').forEach(b => b.addEventListener('click', () => { urlInput.value = b.dataset.url; startDetect(b.dataset.url); }));
      })();
    </script>
  </Fragment>

  <Fragment slot="content">
    <div class="speakable">
      <div class="lead-box">
        <p><strong>The theStacc CMS Detector</strong> identifies the content management system, e-commerce platform, framework, web server, programming language, CDN, hosting platform, analytics tools, and 70+ other technologies powering any website. Enter any URL and get an instant tech stack report with confidence scores, security header checks, and categorized results. The tool is built for SEO professionals, agencies, and business owners who need to understand what they or their competitors are running — for migrations, audits, competitive research, or simply figuring out what a website is built with.</p>
      </div>

      <h2>What Is a CMS and Why Does It Matter?</h2>
      <p>A Content Management System (CMS) is the software that lets you create, edit, and publish web pages without writing HTML by hand. Behind the scenes, it stores your content in a database, generates HTML when someone visits, and gives non-technical users a friendly editor for managing pages, blog posts, products, and media.</p>
      <p>Knowing which CMS a website uses tells you a lot about how it operates. WordPress sites can be extended with plugins and themes, Shopify sites have a fixed e-commerce structure but easy storefront customization, Webflow sites give designers visual control without code, and custom-coded sites offer maximum flexibility but require developer time for every change. The CMS choice affects your SEO options, your content velocity, your hosting costs, and your migration difficulty.</p>
      <p>For agencies, knowing a prospect's CMS upfront saves hours of qualification. For competitive researchers, identifying competitors' stacks reveals what tools are working in your industry. For business owners who inherited a website without documentation, a CMS detector is often the fastest way to figure out what you actually own and what it would take to change anything.</p>

      <h2>How CMS Detection Works</h2>
      <p>Every CMS leaves fingerprints in the pages it generates. Some are intentional, like the <code>&lt;meta name="generator"&gt;</code> tag that WordPress, Drupal, and Astro add to identify themselves. Some are structural, like WordPress's <code>/wp-content/</code> directory paths or Shopify's <code>cdn.shopify.com</code> asset URLs. Some are protocol-level, like Cloudflare's <code>cf-ray</code> header or Vercel's <code>x-vercel-id</code>.</p>
      <p>A good CMS detector aggregates many signal types: HTTP headers from the server response, cookies set on first load, meta tags in the HTML, recognizable markup patterns, the URLs of loaded scripts and stylesheets, and the hostname itself. Each signal contributes to a confidence score. A site that emits the WordPress generator meta tag, sets WordPress login cookies, AND links to <code>/wp-content/</code> assets is almost certainly WordPress. A site with only one weak signal is "possibly" something but might be a false positive.</p>
      <p>Modern frameworks like Next.js, Nuxt, Astro, and SvelteKit are detected via their build artifacts: directories like <code>/_next/static/</code>, <code>/_nuxt/</code>, <code>/_astro/</code>, and global JavaScript variables like <code>__NEXT_DATA__</code> or <code>__NUXT__</code>. CDNs and hosting platforms surface in custom HTTP headers that they always set on every response.</p>

      <h2>What You Can Do With This Information</h2>
      <p><strong>Plan a migration:</strong> If you discover a prospect runs WordPress, you know they can move to a different host with a couple of plugins and a few hours of work. If they run Webflow, migrating means rebuilding from scratch — a different conversation entirely. Quoting accurately starts with knowing what you are quoting against.</p>
      <p><strong>Diagnose SEO issues:</strong> Some CMS configurations have known SEO weaknesses. Default Wix sites historically had limited control over meta tags. Some Shopify themes auto-generate canonical tags incorrectly. Knowing the platform tells you which checklist to run and which specific gotchas to look for.</p>
      <p><strong>Compete more intelligently:</strong> If your top competitor ranks well on Shopify, that tells you Shopify SEO is strong enough to win in your niche — no need to over-engineer. If they run a Next.js stack with custom React components, that signals heavy engineering investment and a different competitive playing field.</p>
      <p><strong>Audit your own site:</strong> Sometimes the answer is "we don't actually know." A site you inherited, a project a former contractor built, a brand acquisition with no docs. The CMS detector is the fastest way to start mapping what you own and where to invest next.</p>

      <h2>CMS Detector Comparison</h2>
      <div class="table-wrap">
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Feature</th><th>theStacc</th><th>Wappalyzer</th><th>BuiltWith</th><th>What CMS</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>Price</td><td>Free</td><td>Freemium</td><td>Paid ($295+/mo)</td><td>Free</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Signup required</td><td>No</td><td>No (extension)</td><td>Yes</td><td>No</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Browser extension needed</td><td>No</td><td>Yes</td><td>No</td><td>No</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Security header check</td><td>Yes — 6 headers</td><td>No</td><td>No</td><td>No</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Confidence scoring</td><td>High / Medium / Low</td><td>Yes</td><td>No</td><td>No</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Category grouping</td><td>Yes — 14 categories</td><td>Yes</td><td>Yes</td><td>Basic</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Detection signal details</td><td>Yes — expandable</td><td>No</td><td>No</td><td>No</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Copy stack to clipboard</td><td>Yes</td><td>No</td><td>Yes</td><td>No</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Linked SEO tools</td><td>Yes — audit, meta tags</td><td>No</td><td>No</td><td>No</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h2>Use Cases by Role</h2>
      <p><strong>SEO Agencies & Consultants.</strong> Before pitching a prospect, run their site through the detector. If they are on WordPress with Elementor, you know exactly which plugins to recommend and what SEO limitations to address. If they are on Shopify, you know the URL structure constraints and which apps handle SEO. This intel turns generic pitches into specific, credible proposals that close faster.</p>
      <p><strong>Web Developers & Freelancers.</strong> When inheriting a project with no documentation, the CMS detector reveals the entire stack in seconds. Is it a custom Next.js app on Vercel? A WordPress site on shared hosting? A Webflow site that the client wants migrated? Knowing the full tech stack — including the CDN, analytics, and marketing tools — lets you scope projects accurately and avoid nasty surprises mid-build.</p>
      <p><strong>Marketing Teams.</strong> Discover which tools your competitors use for analytics, marketing automation, and conversion tracking. If a competitor uses HubSpot, Hotjar, and Intercom, they are running a sophisticated inbound marketing operation. If they use only Google Analytics, there is an opportunity gap. Use this intelligence to benchmark your own martech stack and justify budget for missing tools.</p>
      <p><strong>Business Owners.</strong> If you inherited a website from a former employee, contractor, or acquisition, you may not know what platform it runs on or how to update it. The CMS detector tells you immediately. It also checks security headers, which matters for compliance and customer trust. A site missing basic security headers signals neglect — something to address before it becomes a liability.</p>
      <p><strong>Investors & Acquirers.</strong> Due diligence on digital assets starts with understanding the tech stack. A SaaS company running on a modern Jamstack framework signals engineering maturity. An e-commerce site on a deprecated Magento version signals technical debt and migration risk. The CMS detector gives you this information in seconds, without needing access to the company's internal systems.</p>

      <h2>CMS Choice and SEO Performance</h2>
      <p>All major CMSes can rank well on Google if configured correctly, but each has different default strengths and weaknesses. <strong>WordPress</strong> with a good SEO plugin (Yoast or RankMath) gives you full control over titles, descriptions, schema, redirects, sitemaps, and crawl directives — at the cost of having to maintain plugins and updates. <strong>Shopify</strong> handles e-commerce SEO well by default but limits control over URL structure and some technical SEO features.</p>
      <p><strong>Webflow</strong> gives designers strong control over on-page elements and clean code output, but its CMS collections have caps on item counts and some operations require manual export. <strong>Wix</strong> has improved SEO significantly in recent years with full control over titles, descriptions, structured data, and sitemap. <strong>Squarespace</strong> handles basic SEO well out of the box but offers fewer technical controls than WordPress for advanced cases.</p>
      <p>Modern <strong>Jamstack frameworks</strong> like Astro, Next.js, and SvelteKit produce extremely fast, well-structured sites that rank well on technical merit but require developer involvement for content changes. <strong>Headless CMS</strong> setups (Contentful, Sanity, Strapi powering a custom frontend) combine flexible authoring with custom-built frontend SEO, but cost more to build and maintain.</p>

